trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of integers in a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox"></xref>.

<xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> is a sorted collection to which items are appended by using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Add%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.AddRange%2A> methods.
Duplicate values are removed.
The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> is used mainly by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.CustomTabOffsets%2A> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> class.
You cannot create an instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> class without associating it with a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox> control.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox"></xref> that owns the collection.
Adds a unique integer to the collection in sorted order.
The integer to add to the collection.
The index of the added item.
There is insufficient space available to store the new item.
Adds an array of integers to the collection.
The array of integers is appended to the collection, and duplicates are removed from the collection.
The array of integers to add to the collection.
Adds the contents of an existing <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> to another collection.
The contents of the existing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> are appended to the current collection, and duplicates are removed from the combined collection.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> to add to another collection.
Removes all integers from the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Determines whether the specified integer is in the collection.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Contains%2A> method to determine whether an integer is a member of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection>.

Once you know that the item is located within the collection, you can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.IndexOf%2A> method to determine where the item is located within the collection.
The integer to search for in the collection.
`true` if the specified integer is in the collection; otherwise, `false`.
Copies the entire <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> into an existing array of integers at a specified location within the array.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.CopyTo%2A> method to combine the integers from multiple collections into a single array.
You can then use this array to populate the contents of another <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox> control using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.AddRange%2A> method.
The array into which the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> is copied.
The location within the destination array to which to copy the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Gets the number of selected items in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox"></xref>.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Count%2A> property to determine the number of selected items in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection>.
You can then use this value when you are looping through the items and you need to provide a number of iterations to perform the loop.
The number of selected items in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox"></xref>.
Retrieves the index within the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref> of the specified integer.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.IndexOf%2A> method to determine where an item is located within the collection.
To determine whether an item is located within the collection before calling this method, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Contains%2A> method.
The integer for which to retrieve the index.
The zero-based index of the integer in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>; otherwise, negative one (-1).
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Item(System.Int32)"></xref> having the specified index.
The position of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Item(System.Int32)"></xref> in the collection.
The selected <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Item(System.Int32)"></xref> at the specified position.
Removes the specified integer from the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
When you remove an integer from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection>, the indexes change for subsequent integers in the collection.
All information about the removed integer is deleted.
You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Remove%2A> method to remove a specific item from the list by specifying the actual item to remove from the list.
To specify the index of the integer to remove instead of the integer itself, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.RemoveAt%2A> method.
If the integer is not in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection>, this method does nothing.
The integer to remove from the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Removes the integer at the specified index from the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
When you remove an integer from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection>, the indexes change for subsequent integers in the collection.
All information about the removed integer is deleted.
You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.RemoveAt%2A> method to remove a specific integer from the list by specifying the index of the integer to remove from the list.
To specify the item to remove instead of the index to the item, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection.Remove%2A> method.
The zero-based index of the integer to remove.
Gets a value indicating whether access to the collection is synchronized (thread safe).
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> interface.
`true` in all cases.
Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection of controls.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> interface.
The object used to synchronize to the collection.
Retrieves an enumeration of all the integers in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
This method creates an enumerator that contains a snapshot of the collection.
You can change the collection by changing the enumerator; however, multiple enumerators can simultaneously access the same collection.

Changing the collection (either directly or through another enumerator) can thus cause <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to throw an exception.
Two enumerators created from the same collection at the same time can contain different snapshots.
Removing objects from the enumerator also removes them from the collection.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> for the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Adds a tab stop to the collection.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The tab stop to add to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
The index at which the integer was added to the collection.
item is `null`.
item is not an 32-bit signed integer.
There is insufficient space to store the new item in the collection.
Clears all the tab stops from the collection.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
Determines whether the specified tab stop is in the collection.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The tab stop to locate in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
`true` if item is an integer located in the IntegerCollection; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the index of the specified tab stop in the collection.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.

The tab stop to locate in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
The zero-based index of item if it was found in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>; otherwise, -1.
Inserts an item into the collection at a specified index.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The zero-based index at which value should be inserted.
The object to insert into the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Always thrown.
Gets a value indicating whether the collection has a fixed size.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
`true` in all cases.
Gets a value indicating whether the collection is read-only.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.

`false` in all cases.
Gets or sets the tab stop at the specified index.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The zero-based index that specifies which tab stop to get.
The tab stop that is stored at the specified location in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
The object is not an integer.
Removes the first occurrence of an item from the collection.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.

The object to add to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ListBox.IntegerCollection"></xref>.
Always thrown.
Removes the item at a specified index.

Always thrown.
